20/06/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Italy and Romania have busted a human trafficking ring that is believed to have sexually exploited more than 150 women, including minors, the police announced Friday (June 18th). A total of 14 people were arrested across Romania based on European warrants issued by a court in Milan. In Italy, 26 people were arrested in relation to the same case. According to the police, the group included mostly Romanians, several Italians, an Albanian and an Egyptian. (Ziare - 19/06/10; AFP - 18/06/10)

